{
  "id": "019d442a-0a15-7ca3-b9db-53db39283d2f",
  "content": ": 22px; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 6px; line-height: 1.5;\">\n          Layer 1 is where I learn. Exploring trade-offs, challenging assumptions, making judgment calls. The implementation is the easy part.\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div style=\"display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 20px;\">\n      <div style=\"font-size: 32px; flex-shrink: 0;\">&#128200;</div>\n      <div>\n        <div style=\"font-size: 24px; font-weight: 700;\">Design review prevents rewrites</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size: 22px; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 6px; line-height: 1.5;\">\n          Reviewing the RFC before coding is why 13 PRs merged with 0 rewrites. Catching a flaw in a spec costs minutes. In code, it costs hours.\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div style=\"display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 20px;\">\n      <div style=\"font-size: 32px; flex-shrink: 0;\">&#128024;</div>\n      <div>\n        <div style=\"font-size: 24px; font-weight: 700;\">Research compounds when persisted</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size: 22px; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 6px; line-height: 1.5;\">\n          Saving every brainstorm and rejected alternative means revisiting a topic is faster each time. Knowledge grows across sessions, not within them.\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div style=\"display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 20px;\">\n      <div style=\"font-size: 32px; flex-shrink: 0;\">&#9889;</div>\n      <div>\n        <div style=\"font-size: 24px; font-weight: 700;\">Well-defined issues execute themselves</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size: 22px; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 6px; line-height: 1.5;\">\n          When Layer 1 is thorough, Layer 2 is almost boring. The dev-loop validates, implements, reviews, and merges. That's the point.\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"divider\"></div>\n\n  <div style=\"margin-top: 8px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-secondary);\">\n      Do you have a structured exploration phase,<br>or do you jump straight to code?\n    </div>\n    <div style=\"font-size: 20px; color: var(--text-muted); margin-top: 8px;\">\n      Genuinely curious how people structure the thinking before coding.\n    </div>\n  </div>",
